# DS01 ds01-sync Runner Sudoers
# Grants the CI self-hosted runner account passwordless sudo for ds01-sync ONLY.
# File: /etc/sudoers.d/ds01-sync-runner
#
# The runner must run as `datasciencelab` — the service/owner account that owns
# /opt/ds01-infra, the staging clone, and the SSH keys (see
# .github/workflows/deploy.yml). Do not run the runner as a personal account.
#
# DEPLOYMENT: deploy.sh installs this and validates it with `visudo -c` first;
# or manually:
#   sudo cp .../config/deploy/sudoers.d/ds01-sync-runner /etc/sudoers.d/
#   sudo chmod 440 /etc/sudoers.d/ds01-sync-runner && sudo visudo -c
#
# Narrow by design: exactly ds01-sync, nothing else. Defence in depth — tag
# creation is gated by a GitHub ruleset (admins only) and ds01-sync itself
# validates the --ref format and that it is an ancestor of origin/main.
# Both paths listed because sudo matches literal paths, not canonicalised symlinks.
datasciencelab ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/local/bin/ds01-sync, /opt/ds01-infra/scripts/system/sync.sh
